article.story: NEW YORK -- — Caleb Fields scored 25 points to help Fairfield defeat Manhattan 82-75 on Sunday. Fields added six rebounds for the Stags (12-7, 6-2 Metro Atlantic Athletic Conference). Jalen Leach added 23 points while shooting 9 for 18, including 4 for 7 from beyond the arc, and he also had five steals. Brycen Goodine was 5 of 9 shooting (3 for 5 from 3-point range) to finish with 13 points. Shaquil Bender led the way for the Jaspers (4-12, 1-6) with 21 points. Daniel Rouzan added 13 points and eight rebounds for Manhattan. Perry Cowan also had 12 points. The loss was the Jaspers' ninth straight. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
